OL,3,CTrain crash scene was like 'giant had
OL,4,Cstamped on a toy set', says widow
OL,6,FMary Dunn remembers the morning of
OL,7,FFebruary 28, 2001, when she lost her
OL,8,Fhusband Stephen, like it was yesterday.
OL,10,FStephen Dunn, had risen early for his
OL,11,Fjob as a train driver. By the time
OL,12,FMary woke hours later, sirens were
OL,13,Fblaring outside.
OL,15,FAt 6:12am Stephen's freight train had
OL,16,Fsmashed into a passenger train near
OL,17,FSelby, North Yorkshire, which had
OL,18,Fminutes earlier collided with a car
OL,19,Fwhich had hit an embankment. He died
OL,20,Finstantly.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
